<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  LaunchAgent for the pc-keiba pipeline daily health monitor.

  WHY THIS EXISTS:
    On 2026-06-28 the sync-realtime-data fetch-results pipeline stopped
    processing at JST 15:42 and the regression was not discovered until
    ~22:30 JST (visually, in the viewer). Nothing in the pipeline paged
    the operator — there was no alert, no log threshold, no automation
    that noticed jobs had stalled. This LaunchAgent is the post-mortem
    control: it fires the wrapper script
    `scripts/launchd/pc-keiba-health-monitor.sh` every 15 min during the
    JST racing-day window (09:00-22:59) and pages on patterns of three
    consecutive check failures (~45 min cumulative).

  SCHEDULE:
    StartCalendarInterval entries fire at minute=0,15,30,45 of every JST
    hour from 09 through 22 inclusive (= 14 hours x 4 = 56 fires/day).
    Outside that window the racing pipeline is naturally quiet (deep
    overnight before NAR fixtures land) and we want to avoid alerting on
    expected silence.

    NOTE: macOS launchd's StartCalendarInterval uses the system's local
    timezone (no `TZ` field exists). This plist assumes the Mac is set to
    Asia/Tokyo (JST). The wrapper computes its own JST time via UTC+9 so
    the checks themselves are timezone-safe; only the FIRING TIMES depend
    on system TZ.

  CATCH-UP BEHAVIOUR:
    StartCalendarInterval queues a missed firing on next wake. We do not
    want a flood of replays after a long sleep — the wrapper holds a
    /tmp/pc-keiba-health-monitor.lock so concurrent fires from catch-up
    + the next scheduled tick coalesce.

  STDOUT/STDERR PATHS:
    Literal absolute paths under /Users/kkk4oru/Library/Logs/pc-keiba-health/.

  SECRETS:
    No secrets live in this plist. The wrapper reads
    CLOUDFLARE_DEBUG_TOKEN, CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID from
    /Users/kkk4oru/ghq/github.com/kkkaoru/horse-racing-data/.env,
    PC_KEIBA_ACCESS_CLIENT_ID/SECRET from
    apps/pc-keiba-viewer/.env.local, and NEON_DATABASE_URL from
    apps/local-postgresql/.env.replica at runtime. All credentials are
    masked in the dated log.

  SILENCER:
    `touch /tmp/pc-keiba-health-silenced` to suppress notifications while
    leaving log capture intact. `rm /tmp/pc-keiba-health-silenced` to
    re-arm.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
